verses.text: The words of Agur the son of Jakeh , \add even\add* the prophecy : the man spake unto Ithiel , even unto Ithiel and Ucal ,
Surely I \add am\add* more brutish than \add any\add* man , and have not the understanding of a man.
I neither learned wisdom , nor have the knowledge of the holy.\f + \fr 30.3 \ft have: Heb. know\f*

Who hath ascended up into heaven , or descended ? who hath gathered the wind in his fists ? who hath bound the waters in a garment ? who hath established all the ends of the earth ? what \add is\add* his name , and what \add is\add* his son’s name , if thou canst tell ?
Every word of God \add is\add* pure : he \add is\add* a shield unto them that put their trust in him.\f + \fr 30.5 \ft pure: Heb. purified\f*
Add thou not unto his words , lest he reprove thee, and thou be found a liar. \p
Two \add things\add* have I required of thee; deny me \add them\add* not before I die :\f + \fr 30.7 \ft deny…: Heb. withhold not from me\f*
Remove far from me vanity and lies : give me neither poverty nor riches ; feed me with food convenient for me:\f + \fr 30.8 \ft convenient…: Heb. of my allowance\f*

Lest I be full , and deny \add thee\add*, and say , Who \add is\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*? or lest I be poor , and steal , and take the name of my God \add in vain\add*.\f + \fr 30.9 \ft deny…: Heb. belie thee\f* \p
Accuse not a servant unto his master , lest he curse thee, and thou be found guilty.\f + \fr 30.10 \ft Accuse…: Heb. Hurt not with thy tongue\f*
\add There is\add* a generation \add that\add* curseth their father , and doth not bless their mother.
\add There is\add* a generation \add that are\add* pure in their own eyes , and \add yet\add* is not washed from their filthiness.
\add There is\add* a generation , O how lofty are their eyes ! and their eyelids are lifted up.
\add There is\add* a generation , whose teeth \add are as\add* swords , and their jaw teeth \add as\add* knives , to devour the poor from off the earth , and the needy from \add among\add* men. \p

The horseleach hath two daughters , \add crying\add*, Give , give. There are three \add things that\add* are never satisfied , \add yea\add*, four \add things\add* say not, \add It is\add* enough :\f + \fr 30.15 \ft It is…: Heb. Wealth\f*
The grave ; and the barren womb ; the earth \add that\add* is not filled with water ; and the fire \add that\add* saith not, \add It is\add* enough.

The eye \add that\add* mocketh at \add his\add* father , and despiseth to obey \add his\add* mother , the ravens of the valley shall pick it out , and the young eagles shall eat it.\f + \fr 30.17 \ft the valley: or, the brook\f* \p
There be three \add things which\add* are too wonderful for me, yea, four which I know not:
The way of an eagle in the air ; the way of a serpent upon a rock ; the way of a ship in the midst of the sea ; and the way of a man with a maid.\f + \fr 30.19 \ft midst: Heb. heart\f*
Such \add is\add* the way of an adulterous woman ; she eateth , and wipeth her mouth , and saith , I have done no wickedness.
For three \add things\add* the earth is disquieted , and for four \add which\add* it cannot bear :
For a servant when he reigneth ; and a fool when he is filled with meat ;
For an odious \add woman\add* when she is married ; and an handmaid that is heir to her mistress. \p
There be four \add things which are\add* little upon the earth , but they \add are\add* exceeding wise :\f + \fr 30.24 \ft exceeding…: Heb. wise, made wise\f*
The ants \add are\add* a people not strong , yet they prepare their meat in the summer ;
The conies \add are but\add* a feeble folk , yet make they their houses in the rocks ;
The locusts have no king , yet go they forth all of them by bands ;\f + \fr 30.27 \ft by…: Heb. gathered together\f*
The spider taketh hold with her hands , and is in kings’ palaces. \p
There be three \add things\add* which go well , yea, four are comely in going :
A lion \add which is\add* strongest among beasts , and turneth not away for any;
A greyhound ; an he goat also ; and a king , against whom \add there is\add* no rising up.\f + \fr 30.31 \ft greyhound: or, horse: Heb. girt in the loins\f*
If thou hast done foolishly in lifting up thyself, or if thou hast thought evil , \add lay\add* thine hand upon thy mouth.
Surely the churning of milk bringeth forth butter , and the wringing of the nose bringeth forth blood : so the forcing of wrath bringeth forth strife.
